The paper deals with analyzing and predicting mobility patterns from traffic trajectory data, which involves sequential, personal, and temporal factors. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Databases (cs.DB), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). However, given the focus on embedding models and prediction tasks, cs.SI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DB, cs.IR, and cs.CL.
